title: Film Screening: Apollo 13
description: It had been less than a year since the first man walked on the Moon, but to the American public, Apollo 13 was just another "routine" space flight. That is until the words pierced the immense void of space: "Houston, we have a problem." Stranded in a crippled spacecraft 205,000 miles from Earth, astronauts Jim Lovell, Fred Haise and Jack Swigert fight a desperate battle to survive. Meanwhile, at Mission Control, astronaut Ken Mattingly, flight director Gene Kranz and the efforts of a heroic ground crew race against time - and the odds - to bring the men home.

title: YOUmedia T-Shirt Graphic Design
description: Borrow silhouette concepts to design your own t-shirt by using special apps to photograph unique ideas and edit them on Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop.

title: Tinker Studio
description: Interested in making but you don't know what to create? Every week we will work on a new project using tools like Makey Makey, Solar Cars, Arduino, LEDs, Little Bits and more. You don't have to be a maker to create but you need willingness to try.

title: Journey Through White Sox History
New Voices on the Studs Terkel Radio Archive
description: New Voices on the Studs Terkel Radio Archive empowers youth to use 21st century skills in developing a multi-media exhibit and digital archive, inserting youth voice into the cultural and historical narratives captured by Studs Terkel.

title: YOUmedia Magic: The Gathering
description: Play trading card games, and challenge yourself to build strategies, skills, and imagination through online platforms.

title: Manga Madness!
description: Love manga comics? Create a manga comic book this summer!

title: Underground Feedback Stereo
description: Learn basic recording techniques, music publishing, social media promotion and music production. We will guide you through the process of becoming an independent musician.

title: Teen Challenge Wrap Party
description: Finish earning your teen challenge badges and celebrate with a party!

title: Science Saturday
description: Love science? So do we! Each month over the summer we'll be doing some great science experiments and activities. This month explore air movement by creating an air vortex gun!

title: Introduction to Video & Photography
description: Take your knowledge of video and photography to a new level by planning a solo or group trip to a place of your choice. The trip will require research into a location, a theme, other artists, and planning, but the results will be totally unique!

title: Electronics 101
description: Ever wondered how a light switch works? Or why a bird can sit on a power line without getting shocked? You can get the answers and start making your own basic electronics in just a few minutes! Every Monday through August 24, we'll have a drop-in, hands-on workshop for kids and teens.

title: Lunch Bus
description: The Greater Chicago Food Depository's Summer Lunch Bus brings healthy meals to children 18 and under Monday through Friday from June 22 to September 4 (Except July 3rd).  All meals must be eaten on-site.

title: YOUmedia Open Hours
description: Come hang out and mess around with all our tech gear, including laptops, a 3D printer, a sticker maker and video games. Learn how to make simple crafts like buttons to stop motion animation. Every day is different so feel free to drop in!

title: Teen Summer Challenge Finale Party
description: Come celebrate the end of the Teen Summer Challenge! Share your discoveries and creations, explorations and achievements! Tell us how YOU defied gravity this summer.

title: Teen Book Club: The 5th Wave
description: Earth has been invaded by aliens who are hard to tell apart from humans. When Cassie searches for her younger brother she gets help, but is it from a friend or a foe? The 5th Wave is available at the branch for check out. Ages 11 & up welcome.

title: YOUmedia Teen Space
description: Come hang out, mess around and geek out!

title: YOUmedia New Media Arts in Painting & Drawing
description: Arts and crafts aficionados use Fresh Paint, a new media arts Microsoft app, to paint and draw on canvases in ways that make the end product look like it was handmade.

title: Tactical Tuesday
description: Love games and gaming? Then you need to come meet some other teens with similar interests and check out our PS3 and game collection while you're at it. For teens in grades 9 through 12.

title: Dark Matter Series: Science in Motion
description: Join us for science, crafts, games, Ender's Game book talk, and more!

title: YOUmedia Open Hours
description: Come hang out and mess around with all our tech gear, including laptops, a 3D printer, a sticker maker and video games. Learn how to make simple crafts like buttons to stop motion animation. Every day is different so feel free to drop in!

title: Games Night
description: Have you heard that we have a PS3? We totally have a PS3 with a bunch of games and 5 controllers! Also board games, like Settlers of Catan, and this one card game that maybe doesn't have any rules.

title: Wired Wednesdays: Teen Tech Series
description: Each week, explore different software and forms of technology while expressing yourself creatively. Learn about video and music editing as well as digital media and technology in this engaging drop-in program series for teens in grades 9 to 12.

title: Women Heroes of World War I
description: The years leading up to the Great War witnessed a global intensifying of both nationalism and suffragist endeavors. When the war mobilized women worldwide, some of their contributions became powerful symbols in their government's propaganda efforts as well as in women's rights movements. Kathryn Atwood, author of Women Heroes of World War I, will highlight the stories of women whose wartime work was utilized in these two ways. Books will be available for purchase.

title: Explore and Soar Extravaganza
description: Come to this party and awards ceremony to celebrate our astronomical achievements during the Explore and Soar Summer Learning Challenge. Enjoy games, crafts, and raffle prizes. Supernova achievers will get to "moonpie" the children's librarian in the face. All participants will receive a certificate.

title: Stylish Saturdays
description: You're a star and you can make sure everyone knows it with your own DIY constellation scarf! We'll be learning about to great ways to personalize clothing, stamping and embroidery.
